<ul class="table-view">
  <li>
    <p>The ORKS app is a mobile application which enables you to record wildlife sightings in Cornwall and Scilly on the go. You can log your sighting with details, photos, descriptions and other information, and upload this to the <a href="https://www.orks.org.uk">www.ORKS.org.uk</a> website.</p>
    <p>Your wildlife records are then available for conservation, sustainable planning, education and research work in Cornwall.
    </p>
    <p class="table-view-cell--centered">ORKS website and app are developed and supported by ERCCIS<br />
      Environmental Records Centre for
      Cornwall and the Isles of Scilly<br />
      <a href="https://www.erccis.org.uk">www.erccis.org.uk</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><strong>Who can use the app?</strong></p>
    <p>We encourage everyone and anyone to use this app, to record and submit your wildlife sightings while out enjoying the Cornish wild places.</p>
    <p>You don’t have to be an expert, this app is for anyone with an interest in wildlife and who want to do more to protect Cornwall’s Wildlife and Wild Places.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><strong>How to use this app</strong></p>
    <p>The ORKS app is linked to the Online Recording Kernow and Scilly website - <a href="https://www.orks.org.uk">www.ORKS.org.uk</a>. Your account and sightings submitted through the app can be viewed and managed through the ORKS website.</p>
    <p>Sign in or register an account on ORKS so you can submit your records:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Add species sightings by going to the '<span class="icon icon-plus icon-inline-orks"></span>' icon</li>
      <li>Add all the details for the sightings, and photos from your device camera or gallery. The location of your sightings is obtained through your phone GPS but can be updated using the map.</li>
      <li>Once your record is correct and you've added all the details you want it is ready to submit; click on the paper-plane icon <span class="icon icon-send icon-inline-orks"></span> to submit it to the ORKS website.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><strong>Development</strong></p>
    <p>This app was developed using open source code for the iRecord app. Developed by ERCCIS and funding by the Alexanda Fund for Recorders.</p>
